<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Tonal center: A minor (Aeolian mode on A in C major key signature). Piece begins and ends on Am.
- Section 1 (bars 1-8): Sparse opening — 3-note LH (A2 E3 A3), simple RH two-voice. Establishes Aeolian color.
- Section 1 repeat (bars 9-16): Same melody, fuller 4-note LH chords. RH explores higher register (E5).
- Section 2 (bars 17-24): New material emphasizes C major and reaches climax at bars 21-22 (RH at G5).
- Section 3 (bars 25-32): Return of opening material with varied voicings. Final Am cadence with full open voicing.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH in section 2 ascends stepwise C5→D5→E5→F5→G5 over bars 17-22, mirroring the melody's push to high E5
- LH contrary motion: when melody rises bar 17, bass steps up D2→D2 (Dm), creating contrary ascent feeling
- Bars 29-30: RH descends E5-B4-G4-D5 in wavering figure; LH steady Am-Em pattern creates rhythmic stability

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-8: Sparse, 3-voice (melody + 2-voice LH) — delicate, intimate
- Bars 9-16: Moderate, 4-voice LH, 2-voice RH — growing confidence
- Bars 17-24: Full texture, RH climbs to G5/C5 register — emotional peak
- Bars 25-32: Return to intimate, then brief final surge into Am cadence
-->
